1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:03,330
The opinions of these people can be poison.

2
00:00:03,920 --> 00:00:08,690
Develop a defense against people who want to convince you that you can't do it.

3
00:00:08,960 --> 00:00:14,130
Accept negative advice only as a challenge to prove that you can do it.

4
00:00:16,240 --> 00:00:19,010
Be extra, extra cautious about this.

5
00:00:19,200 --> 00:00:25,730
Don't let negative thinking people, negators, destroy your plan to think yourself to success.

6
00:00:26,160 --> 00:00:32,690
Negators are everywhere, and they seem to delight in sabotaging the positive progress of others.

7
00:00:33,360 --> 00:00:38,289
During college, I buddied for a couple of semesters with W.W.

8
00:00:38,560 --> 00:00:43,810
He was a fine friend, the kind of fellow who would loan you a little money when you were short,

9
00:00:43,840 --> 00:00:45,970
or help you in many little ways.

10
00:00:46,320 --> 00:00:55,970
Despite this fine loyalty, W.W. was just about one hundred percent sour and bitter toward life, the future, opportunity.

11
00:00:56,240 --> 00:00:58,130
He was a real negator.

12
00:00:58,720 --> 00:01:07,889
During that period, I was an enthusiastic reader of a certain newspaper columnist, who stressed hope, the positive approach, opportunity.

13
00:01:08,240 --> 00:01:13,570
When W.W. would find me reading this columnist, or when her column was mentioned,

14
00:01:13,600 --> 00:01:18,690
he'd swing verbally and say, Oh, for Pete's sake, Dave, read the front page.

15
00:01:18,720 --> 00:01:20,610
That's where you learn about life.

16
00:01:20,720 --> 00:01:26,929
You ought to know that columnist is just making a quick buck, dishing out sweet sauce for the week.

17
00:01:27,280 --> 00:01:34,210
When our discussions turned to getting ahead in life, W.W. was right there with his money-making formula.

18
00:01:34,400 --> 00:01:36,850
In his own words, it went like this.

19
00:01:37,440 --> 00:01:41,010
Dave, there are just three ways to make money these days.

20
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:43,250
One, marry a rich woman.

21
00:01:43,440 --> 00:01:46,929
Two, steal in a nice, clean, legal way.

22
00:01:46,960 --> 00:01:51,810
Or three, get to know the right people, somebody with plenty of pull.

23
00:01:52,800 --> 00:01:57,570
W.W. was always prepared to defend his formula with examples.

24
00:01:57,680 --> 00:02:07,570
Sticking to the front page, he was quick to cite that one labor leader in a thousand who had siphoned off a pile of money from the union till and got away with it.

25
00:02:07,840 --> 00:02:13,490
He kept his eyes open for that rare, rare marriage of the fruit picker to Miss Millionaire.

26
00:02:13,760 --> 00:02:21,169
And he knew a fellow who knew a fellow who knew a big man and got cut in on a big deal that made him rich.

27
00:02:22,080 --> 00:02:28,210
W.W. was several years older than I, and he made excellent grades in his engineering classes.

28
00:02:28,400 --> 00:02:31,409
I looked up to him in a younger brother sort of way.

29
00:02:31,840 --> 00:02:41,010
I came dangerously close to ditching my basic convictions about what it takes to be a success and accepting the negator's philosophy.

30
00:02:41,520 --> 00:02:47,649
Fortunately, one evening after a long discussion with W.W., I grabbed hold of myself.

31
00:02:47,840 --> 00:02:49,840
It dawned on me that I was listening to the voice of failure.
